            <p style={{ color: "#94a3b8" }}>Constraints are non-negotiable boundaries set by business reality, regulation, or physics. Unlike NFRs (which describe desired quality), constraints describe hard limits. The best architecture is the one that achieves the most within its constraints.</p>

