                { color: "#10b981", icon: "🌍", title: "Regional & Compliance Constraints", body: "GDPR requires EU user data to remain in EU (data residency). HIPAA requires PHI encryption and audit logs. PCI-DSS requires payment data isolation. These mandate multi-region architectures with strict data routing and sometimes completely separate infrastructure per region." },
                { color: "#8b5cf6", icon: "👥", title: "Team Constraints", body: "A 3-person team cannot operate a 30-microservice architecture. The number of services you maintain should roughly scale with your team. Conway's Law: your system architecture mirrors your org chart. Size your complexity to your team's operational capacity." },
                { color: "#f43f5e", icon: "⏰", title: "Time-to-Market Constraints", body: "A 6-week launch deadline precludes building a custom distributed database. Use managed services. Premature optimization is the enemy of shipping. Design the simplest thing that meets current requirements, with extension points for future scale." },
